provenance.note:
The early history of the manuscript is not known.  
                    Acquired by Dante Gabriel Rossetti by 1868;
                    acquired by William Michael Rossetti and given to Leonard Erskine Hill sometime before 1919;
                    his wife, Janet Alexander Hill, acquired the manuscript no later than September 1931;
                    offered for sale by the dealer James Rimell & Son (catalogue no. 288, item 64) 
                    along with Blake’s pencil drawing *Queen Katharine, Awakening from Her Dream, after Fuseli* for £225 in 1933;
                    offered by the dealer A.C. Stonehill with the drawing *Queen Katharine* in July 1937;
                    acquired by Lessing J. Rosenwald no later than 1939 and given to the National Gallery of 
                    Art, Washington D.C., in 1943.
